The paper proposes a logic on words that has applications to spanners, a formalism for extracting structured data from text that has recently received considerable attention in database theory. This suggests that the paper could belong to the categories of logic (cs.LO), databases (cs.DB), formal languages and automata theory (cs.FL), data structures and algorithms (cs.DS), or computational complexity (cs.CC). However, since the paper focuses on a logic on words and its applications to spanners, it is most likely to belong to the categories of logic (cs.LO) or databases (cs.DB), followed by formal languages and automata theory (cs.FL), data structures and algorithms (cs.DS), and computational complexity (cs.CC).
